In your example, `ParentName` is captured by value, which means a copy of the variable is made at the time the lambda expression is created. Any changes made to the lambda expression's copy of `ParentName` will not affect the original `ParentName` variable.

If you want the lambda expression to see changes made to `ParentName`, you should capture it by reference. To do this, you can use the `ref` keyword when declaring the variable:

```csharp
public void SomeMethod(string ParentName)
{
